"{\"value\":{\"mdx\":\"# Wallet Setup\\n\\nTo manage your accounts, issue orders, and perform other operations that are required to be signed, a Wallet is required. To instantiate a Wallet, you must first have your associated __mnemonic__.\\n\\n:::details[Unification Plan]\\n- The Python client requires the use of an address to setup the Wallet. However, the address can only be fetched using a Wallet. The address is derived from the mnemonic (address < public key < private key < mnemonic).\\n- Wallet, accounts, subaccounts are all handled differently among the clients. Probably the Rust client handles this best, giving the user more control:\\n    1. There is a `Wallet`;\\n    2. The `Wallet` is used to derive an `Account` by index (each `Account` is associated with a keypair);\\n    3. An `Account` is used to derive a `Subaccount` by index. A `Subaccount` is employed to create orders.  \\n:::\\n\\n::::steps\\n\\n## Getting the mnemonic\\n\\nA Wallet is setup using your secret __mnemonic__ phrase. A __mnemonic__ is a set of 24 words to back up and access your account.\\n\\nYou can fetch your __mnemonic__ from the [dYdX Frontend](https://dydx.trade). After logging in, follow the instructions in \\\"Export secret phrase\\\", accessed by clicking your address in the upper right corner.\\n\\nFor the purpose of this guide, lets copy and store the __mnemonic__ in a `mnemonic.txt` file. \\n\\n:::warning\\nHandle your __mnemonic__ in a secure manner. __Do not share__ it with other parties. Do not commit your __mnemonic__ to a public VCS like GitHub. Access to your __mnemonic__ provides access to your account and funds. \\n:::\\n\\n## Read the mnemonic\\n\\nLets start coding. Load the mnemonic into a string variable. This assumes the mnemonic is stored in a text file.\\n\\n:::code-group\\n\\n```python [Python]\\nmnemonic = open('mnemonic.txt').read().strip()\\n```\\n\\n```typescript [TypeScript]\\nconst mnemonic = require('fs').readFileSync('mnemonic.txt', 'utf8').trim();\\n```\\n\\n```rust [Rust]\\nlet mnemonic = std::fs::read_to_string(\\\"mnemonic.txt\\\").unwrap().trim().to_string();\\n```\\n\\n:::\\n\\n## Create the Wallet\\n\\nUse the __mnemonic__ to create a Wallet instance capable of signing transactions.\\n\\n:::code-group\\n\\n```python [Python]\\nfrom dydx_v4_client.key_pair import KeyPair\\nfrom dydx_v4_client.wallet import Wallet\\n\\n# Define your address.\\naddress = Wallet(KeyPair.from_mnemonic(mnemonic), 0, 0).address()\\n\\n# Create a Wallet with updated parameters required for trading\\nwallet = await Wallet.from_mnemonic(node, mnemonic, address)\\n```\\n\\n```typescript [TypeScript]\\nimport { BECH32_PREFIX, LocalWallet } from '@dydxprotocol/v4-client-js';\\n\\nconst wallet = await LocalWallet.fromMnemonic(mnemonic, BECH32_PREFIX);\\n```\\n\\n```rust [Rust]\\nuse dydx::node::Wallet;\\n\\nlet wallet = Wallet::from_mnemonic(&mnemonic)?;\\n```\\n\\n:::\\n\\n:::note\\nPlease check the list of [available endpoints here](/interaction/endpoints#endpoints).\\n:::\\n\\n## Instantiate a Subaccount\\n\\n:::note\\nThis step is not required in the Python client.\\n:::\\n\\nWhen issuing orders, the relevant Subaccount must be chosen to place the order under. A Subaccount is associated with an Account, and is meant to provide trade isolation against your other Subaccounts and enhance funds management.\\nSee more about [Accounts and Subaccounts](/concepts/trading/accounts).\\n\\n:::code-group\\n\\n```python [Python]\\n# Not required. The `wallet` instance created above already contains the necessary information.\\n# The Subaccount to be used is defined using an integer when creating an order.\\n```\\n\\n```typescript [TypeScript]\\nimport { SubaccountInfo } from '@dydxprotocol/v4-client-js';\\n\\nconst subaccount = new SubaccountInfo(wallet, 0);\\n```\\n\\n```rust [Rust]\\n// Create an `Account` instance for the account index 0. This `Account` has updated parameters required for trading.\\nlet account = wallet.account(0, &mut node).await?;\\n\\n// Create a `Subaccount` instance for the subaccount index 0.\\nlet subaccount = account.subaccount(0)?;\\n```\\n\\n:::\\n\\n:::info\\nBy default, both Python and TypeScript client Wallets will derive and use the Account indexed at 0.\\n:::\\n\\n\",\"document\":[{\"href\":\"/interaction/wallet-setup#wallet-setup\",\"html\":\"</header>\\n<p>To manage your accounts, issue orders, and perform other operations that are required to be signed, a Wallet is required. To instantiate a Wallet, you must first have your associated <strong>mnemonic</strong>.</p>\\n<details><summary>Unification Plan</summary><ul>\\n<li>The Python client requires the use of an address to setup the Wallet. However, the address can only be fetched using a Wallet. The address is derived from the mnemonic (address &lt; public key &lt; private key &lt; mnemonic).</li>\\n<li>Wallet, accounts, subaccounts are all handled differently among the clients. Probably the Rust client handles this best, giving the user more control:\\n<ol>\\n<li>There is a <code>Wallet</code>;</li>\\n<li>The <code>Wallet</code> is used to derive an <code>Account</code> by index (each <code>Account</code> is associated with a keypair);</li>\\n<li>An <code>Account</code> is used to derive a <code>Subaccount</code> by index. A <code>Subaccount</code> is employed to create orders.</li>\\n</ol>\\n</li>\\n</ul></details>\\n<div data-vocs-steps=\\\"true\\\"><div data-depth=\\\"2\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/wallet-setup.mdx#wallet-setup\",\"isPage\":true,\"text\":\"\\nTo manage your accounts, issue orders, and perform other operations that are required to be signed, a Wallet is required. To instantiate a Wallet, you must first have your associated mnemonic.\\nUnification Plan\\nThe Python client requires the use of an address to setup the Wallet. However, the address can only be fetched using a Wallet. The address is derived from the mnemonic (address &lt; public key &lt; private key &lt; mnemonic).\\nWallet, accounts, subaccounts are all handled differently among the clients. Probably the Rust client handles this best, giving the user more control:\\n\\nThere is a Wallet;\\nThe Wallet is used to derive an Account by index (each Account is associated with a keypair);\\nAn Account is used to derive a Subaccount by index. A Subaccount is employed to create orders.\\n\\n\\n\\n\",\"title\":\"Wallet Setup\",\"titles\":[]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/wallet-setup#getting-the-mnemonic\",\"html\":\"<p>A Wallet is setup using your secret <strong>mnemonic</strong> phrase. A <strong>mnemonic</strong> is a set of 24 words to back up and access your account.</p><p>You can fetch your <strong>mnemonic</strong> from the <a href=\\\"https://dydx.trade\\\">dYdX Frontend</a>. After logging in, follow the instructions in &quot;Export secret phrase&quot;, accessed by clicking your address in the upper right corner.</p><p>For the purpose of this guide, lets copy and store the <strong>mnemonic</strong> in a <code>mnemonic.txt</code> file.</p><aside data-callout=\\\"warning\\\"><p>Handle your <strong>mnemonic</strong> in a secure manner. <strong>Do not share</strong> it with other parties. Do not commit your <strong>mnemonic</strong> to a public VCS like GitHub. Access to your <strong>mnemonic</strong> provides access to your account and funds.</p></aside></div><div data-depth=\\\"2\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/wallet-setup.mdx#getting-the-mnemonic\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"A Wallet is setup using your secret mnemonic phrase. A mnemonic is a set of 24 words to back up and access your account.You can fetch your mnemonic from the dYdX Frontend. After logging in, follow the instructions in &quot;Export secret phrase&quot;, accessed by clicking your address in the upper right corner.For the purpose of this guide, lets copy and store the mnemonic in a mnemonic.txt file.Handle your mnemonic in a secure manner. Do not share it with other parties. Do not commit your mnemonic to a public VCS like GitHub. Access to your mnemonic provides access to your account and funds.\",\"title\":\"Getting the mnemonic\",\"titles\":[\"Wallet Setup\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/wallet-setup#read-the-mnemonic\",\"html\":\"<p>Lets start coding. Load the mnemonic into a string variable. This assumes the mnemonic is stored in a text file.</p><div class=\\\"code-group\\\"><div data-title=\\\"Python\\\"><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" data-title=\\\"Python\\\" data-lang=\\\"python\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">mnemonic </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">=</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> open</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&#x27;mnemonic.txt&#x27;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">).read().strip()</span></span></code></pre></div><div data-title=\\\"TypeScript\\\"><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" data-title=\\\"TypeScript\\\" data-lang=\\\"typescript\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">const</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> mnemonic</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\"> =</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\"> require</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&#x27;fs&#x27;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">).</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">readFileSync</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&#x27;mnemonic.txt&#x27;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">, </span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&#x27;utf8&#x27;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">).</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">trim</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">();</span></span></code></pre></div><div data-title=\\\"Rust\\\"><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" data-title=\\\"Rust\\\" data-lang=\\\"rust\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">let</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> mnemonic </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">=</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\"> std</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">::</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\">fs</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">::</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">read_to_string</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&quot;mnemonic.txt&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">)</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">.</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">unwrap</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">()</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">.</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">trim</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">()</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">.</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">to_string</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">();</span></span></code></pre></div></div></div><div data-depth=\\\"2\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/wallet-setup.mdx#read-the-mnemonic\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"Lets start coding. Load the mnemonic into a string variable. This assumes the mnemonic is stored in a text file.mnemonic = open(&#x27;mnemonic.txt&#x27;).read().strip()const mnemonic = require(&#x27;fs&#x27;).readFileSync(&#x27;mnemonic.txt&#x27;, &#x27;utf8&#x27;).trim();let mnemonic = std::fs::read_to_string(&quot;mnemonic.txt&quot;).unwrap().trim().to_string();\",\"title\":\"Read the mnemonic\",\"titles\":[\"Wallet Setup\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/wallet-setup#create-the-wallet\",\"html\":\"<p>Use the <strong>mnemonic</strong> to create a Wallet instance capable of signing transactions.</p><div class=\\\"code-group\\\"><div data-title=\\\"Python\\\"><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" data-title=\\\"Python\\\" data-lang=\\\"python\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">from</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> dydx_v4_client.key_pair </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">import</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> KeyPair</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">from</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> dydx_v4_client.wallet </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">import</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> Wallet</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\" data-empty-line=\\\"true\\\"> </span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\"># Define your address.</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">address </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">=</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> Wallet(KeyPair.from_mnemonic(mnemonic), </span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\">0</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">, </span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\">0</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">).address()</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\" data-empty-line=\\\"true\\\"> </span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\"># Create a Wallet with updated parameters required for trading</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">wallet </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">=</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\"> await</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> Wallet.from_mnemonic(node, mnemonic, address)</span></span></code></pre></div><div data-title=\\\"TypeScript\\\"><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" data-title=\\\"TypeScript\\\" data-lang=\\\"typescript\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">import</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> { BECH32_PREFIX, LocalWallet } </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">from</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> &#x27;@dydxprotocol/v4-client-js&#x27;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">;</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\" data-empty-line=\\\"true\\\"> </span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">const</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> wallet</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\"> =</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\"> await</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> LocalWallet.</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">fromMnemonic</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(mnemonic, </span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\">BECH32_PREFIX</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">);</span></span></code></pre></div><div data-title=\\\"Rust\\\"><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" data-title=\\\"Rust\\\" data-lang=\\\"rust\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">use</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\"> dydx</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">::</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\">node</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">::</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\">Wallet</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">;</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\" data-empty-line=\\\"true\\\"> </span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">let</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> wallet </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">=</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\"> Wallet</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">::</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">from_mnemonic</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">&amp;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">mnemonic)</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">?</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">;</span></span></code></pre></div></div><aside data-callout=\\\"note\\\"><p>Please check the list of <a href=\\\"/interaction/endpoints#endpoints\\\">available endpoints here</a>.</p></aside></div><div data-depth=\\\"2\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/wallet-setup.mdx#create-the-wallet\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"Use the mnemonic to create a Wallet instance capable of signing transactions.from dydx_v4_client.key_pair import KeyPair\\nfrom dydx_v4_client.wallet import Wallet\\n \\n# Define your address.\\naddress = Wallet(KeyPair.from_mnemonic(mnemonic), 0, 0).address()\\n \\n# Create a Wallet with updated parameters required for trading\\nwallet = await Wallet.from_mnemonic(node, mnemonic, address)import { BECH32_PREFIX, LocalWallet } from &#x27;@dydxprotocol/v4-client-js&#x27;;\\n \\nconst wallet = await LocalWallet.fromMnemonic(mnemonic, BECH32_PREFIX);use dydx::node::Wallet;\\n \\nlet wallet = Wallet::from_mnemonic(&amp;mnemonic)?;Please check the list of available endpoints here.\",\"title\":\"Create the Wallet\",\"titles\":[\"Wallet Setup\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/wallet-setup#instantiate-a-subaccount\",\"html\":\"<aside data-callout=\\\"note\\\"><p>This step is not required in the Python client.</p></aside><p>When issuing orders, the relevant Subaccount must be chosen to place the order under. A Subaccount is associated with an Account, and is meant to provide trade isolation against your other Subaccounts and enhance funds management.\\nSee more about <a href=\\\"/concepts/trading/accounts\\\">Accounts and Subaccounts</a>.</p><div class=\\\"code-group\\\"><div data-title=\\\"Python\\\"><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" data-title=\\\"Python\\\" data-lang=\\\"python\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\"># Not required. The `wallet` instance created above already contains the necessary information.</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\"># The Subaccount to be used is defined using an integer when creating an order.</span></span></code></pre></div><div data-title=\\\"TypeScript\\\"><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" data-title=\\\"TypeScript\\\" data-lang=\\\"typescript\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">import</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> { SubaccountInfo } </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">from</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> &#x27;@dydxprotocol/v4-client-js&#x27;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">;</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\" data-empty-line=\\\"true\\\"> </span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">const</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> subaccount</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\"> =</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\"> new</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\"> SubaccountInfo</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(wallet, </span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\">0</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">);</span></span></code></pre></div><div data-title=\\\"Rust\\\"><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" data-title=\\\"Rust\\\" data-lang=\\\"rust\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\">// Create an `Account` instance for the account index 0. This `Account` has updated parameters required for trading.</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">let</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> account </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">=</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> wallet</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">.</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">account</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\">0</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">, </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">&amp;mut</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> node)</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">.await?</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">;</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\" data-empty-line=\\\"true\\\"> </span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\">// Create a `Subaccount` instance for the subaccount index 0.</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">let</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> subaccount </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">=</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> account</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">.</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">subaccount</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\">0</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">)</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">?</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">;</span></span></code></pre></div></div><aside data-callout=\\\"info\\\"><p>By default, both Python and TypeScript client Wallets will derive and use the Account indexed at 0.</p></aside></div></div>\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/wallet-setup.mdx#instantiate-a-subaccount\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"This step is not required in the Python client.When issuing orders, the relevant Subaccount must be chosen to place the order under. A Subaccount is associated with an Account, and is meant to provide trade isolation against your other Subaccounts and enhance funds management.\\nSee more about Accounts and Subaccounts.# Not required. The `wallet` instance created above already contains the necessary information.\\n# The Subaccount to be used is defined using an integer when creating an order.import { SubaccountInfo } from &#x27;@dydxprotocol/v4-client-js&#x27;;\\n \\nconst subaccount = new SubaccountInfo(wallet, 0);// Create an `Account` instance for the account index 0. This `Account` has updated parameters required for trading.\\nlet account = wallet.account(0, &amp;mut node).await?;\\n \\n// Create a `Subaccount` instance for the subaccount index 0.\\nlet subaccount = account.subaccount(0)?;By default, both Python and TypeScript client Wallets will derive and use the Account indexed at 0.\",\"title\":\"Instantiate a Subaccount\",\"titles\":[\"Wallet Setup\"]}]}}"
